Steps to Execute the Script

Activate the Virtual Environment:

Open a terminal.
Navigate to your project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd /Users/talia.rosenkranz/PycharmProjects/inWed_bot

Activate the virtual environment:
bash
Copy code
source inWedEnv/bin/activate

Run ngrok (Keep it Open in a Separate Terminal):
Open a new terminal.
Run ngrok to expose your local server:
bash
Copy code
ngrok http 5000
Keep this terminal open and note the ngrok URL (e.g., https://abcd1234.ngrok.io).

Activate Virtual Environment Again (in a New Terminal):
Open another terminal.
Navigate to your project directory again:
bash
Copy code
cd /Users/talia.rosenkranz/PycharmProjects/inWed_bot

Activate the virtual environment again:
bash
Copy code
source inWedEnv/bin/activate
Run the Python Script:

In the terminal with the virtual environment activated, run the Python script:
bash
Copy code
python3 inWed_bot.py

Trigger Message Sending:
Open your browser and go to:
perl
Copy code
http://127.0.0.1:5000/send-message

